      • type1Calc

        public BillOfMaterials type1Calc​(int length,
                                 int width)
                          throws java.sql.SQLException,
                                 java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        Parameters:
        length - in cm The chosen length of a customer's carport.
        width - in cm The chosen width of a customer's carport.
        Returns:
        A BillOfMaterials object is returned, containing the aforementioned arraylist. This object is used to add the bill of materials to the database (this happens in the FlatOrder class in the PresentationLayer directory).
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - Thrown if the provided SQL string in each method has incorrect syntax, unknown keywords etc. or if the connection to the database cannot be established.
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - Thrown from Connector if the "Class.forName" method doesn't find the specified class (JDBC driver in this case).

      • calcOptimalLengthOfMaterial

        public int calcOptimalLengthOfMaterial​(int measurement,
                                       int materialId)
                                throws java.sql.SQLException,
                                       java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        Parameters:
        measurement - in cm A value used to determine the optimal length of a material for a specified measurement (typically length or width of the shed).
        materialId - In order for the getMaterialLengths method to return the correct lengths for the material we want the optimal length of, we need to know its ID in the database.
        Returns:
        The calculated optimal length of a material for a given measurement.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - Thrown if the provided SQL string in each method has incorrect syntax, unknown keywords etc. or if the connection to the database cannot be established.
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - Thrown from Connector if the "Class.forName" method doesn't find the specified class (JDBC driver in this case).

      • calcLengthAndAmountOfTrapezPlates

        public int calcLengthAndAmountOfTrapezPlates​(int length,
                                             int width,
                                             java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> measurements)
        Parameters:
        length - in cm The chosen length of a customer's carport.
        width - in cm The chosen width of a customer's carport.
        measurements - An arraylist of lengths for a material. The getMaterialLengths() method is used to get the lengths of the roofplates in the type1Calc and type2Calc methods like it was in the calcOptimalLengthOfMaterial method.
        Returns:
        This method returns the number of roofplates needed to cover the entire roof of the carport. If a secondary plate length is needed, the amount of plates needed is equal to the amount of primary plates. This is not obvious here, but can be seen on the bill of materials page on the website.
